Intersector.overlapConvexPolygon(a,b,mtv) is returning the same mtv.normal and mtv.depth regardless of the side of the intersection (In the example below the expected mtv for testBlock should have inverse signs.)

Intersector.overlapConexPolygon(a,b,mtv) is returning different mtv.normal values (Sign swap) based on the ordering of the vertexes.

``` java
Polygon testBlock;
Polygon polygon;
testBlock  = new Polygon(new float[]{0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0});
polygon = new Polygon(new float[]{0, 0, 1, 4, 2, 4, 1, 0});
Intersector.overlapConvexPolygons(testBlock, polygon, mtv);
System.out.println(mtv.normal + "-" + mtv.depth); //[-0.97014254:0.24253564]-0.97014254
testBlock.setPosition(1, 3);
Intersector.overlapConvexPolygons(testBlock, polygon, mtv);
System.out.println(mtv.normal + "-" + mtv.depth);//[-0.97014254:0.24253564]-0.97014254

testBlock  = new Polygon(new float[]{0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0});
polygon = new Polygon(new float[]{1, 4, 2, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0});
Intersector.overlapConvexPolygons(testBlock, polygon, mtv);
System.out.println(mtv.normal + "-" + mtv.depth);//[0.97014254:-0.24253564]-0.97014254
testBlock.setPosition(1, 3);
Intersector.overlapConvexPolygons(testBlock, polygon, mtv);
System.out.println(mtv.normal + "-" + mtv.depth);//[0.97014254:-0.24253564]-0.97014254

testBlock  = new Polygon(new float[]{0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0});
polygon = new Polygon(new float[]{2, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4});
Intersector.overlapConvexPolygons(testBlock, polygon, mtv);
System.out.println(mtv.normal + "-" + mtv.depth);//[0.97014254:-0.24253564]-0.97014254
testBlock.setPosition(1, 3);
Intersector.overlapConvexPolygons(testBlock, polygon, mtv);
System.out.println(mtv.normal + "-" + mtv.depth);//[0.97014254:-0.24253564]-0.97014254

testBlock  = new Polygon(new float[]{0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0});
polygon = new Polygon(new float[]{1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, 2, 4});
Intersector.overlapConvexPolygons(testBlock, polygon, mtv);
System.out.println(mtv.normal + "-" + mtv.depth);//[-0.97014254:0.24253564]-0.97014254
testBlock.setPosition(1, 3);
Intersector.overlapConvexPolygons(testBlock, polygon, mtv);
System.out.println(mtv.normal + "-" + mtv.depth);//[-0.97014254:0.24253564]-0.97014254
